---
id: org.dxos.plugin.gallery
name: GalleryPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A simple image gallery plugin for `DXOS` Composer.
A `Gallery` is an ECHO object containing an array of images referenced
by URL — either an external `http(s)://` URL or a `wnfs://` URL backed
by the WNFS file uploader plugin.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |

## Types

```mdl
type Image
  fields:
    url: string                # http(s):// or wnfs:// URL
    type?: string              # MIME type (e.g. image/png)
    name?: string              # Original file name
    description?: string       # Optional alt / caption
    width?: number
    height?: number
```

```mdl
type Gallery
  fields:
    name?: string
    images: Image[]
```

## Components

```mdl
component GalleryArticle
  desc: Main article surface for a Gallery — Panel + Toolbar + Masonry of image cards.
  props:
    gallery: Gallery
  state:
    uploading: boolean
  actions:
    addImage()                 # Opens a file picker, uploads via WNFS, appends Image
    removeImage(index: number)
    show()                     # Enters fullscreen presentation mode
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [add] [show] …          │  ← Toolbar (MenuBuilder)
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ ┌───┐ ┌───┐ ┌───┐       │
    │ │img│ │img│ │img│  …    │  ← Masonry of GalleryImage cards
    │ └───┘ └───┘ └───┘       │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component GalleryShow
  desc: Fullscreen presentation surface for a Gallery — masonry filling the viewport.
  props:
    gallery: Gallery
  emits:
    onExit()
```

```mdl
component GalleryImage
  desc: A single image tile rendered as a Card with poster + delete button.
  props:
    image: Image
  emits:
    onDelete()
```

## Operations

```mdl
op describeImage
  desc: |
    Generate a textual description for an image and write it to the
    `description` field. Placeholder implementation — generates a stub
    description until the AI service grows native image-to-text support.
  input:
    gallery: Ref<Gallery>
    index: number             # Index of the image within gallery.images
  output:
    description: string
  effects: [echo:write]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Add Image

  req F-1.1:
    when: user clicks the "Add" toolbar button
    then: a file picker opens accepting image MIME types

  req F-1.2:
    when: user selects an image file
    then: file is uploaded via the FileUploader capability (WNFS) and
          the resulting URL appended to gallery.images

  req F-1.3:
    when: no FileUploader capability is registered
    then: the "Add" toolbar button is disabled
```

```mdl
feat F-2: View Gallery

  req F-2.1: Images render as cards in a Masonry layout.
  req F-2.2: Cards display the image as a poster.
  req F-2.3: Each card exposes a delete affordance that removes the
             image from gallery.images on confirmation.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Fullscreen Show

  req F-3.1:
    when: user clicks the "Show" toolbar button
    then: gallery enters fullscreen presentation mode via plugin-deck's
          `solo--fullscreen` adjustment, opening the `GalleryShow`
          companion surface.

  req F-3.2:
    when: user exits fullscreen
    then: viewport returns to the article surface.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Describe Image

  req F-4.1:
    when: op:describeImage is invoked
    then: gallery.images[index].description is populated with a
          generated description.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Add image via WNFS
  given: a Gallery, FileUploader capability registered
  when: user picks an image from the toolbar add button
  then:
    - file uploaded; FileInfo.url returned
    - gallery.images contains a new Image with that url
```

```mdl
test T-2: Add disabled without uploader
  given: a Gallery, no FileUploader capability registered
  then: the Add toolbar button is disabled
```

```mdl
test T-3: Delete image
  given: a Gallery with 3 images
  when: user clicks the delete button on the second card
  then: gallery.images has 2 entries; the deleted image is gone
```

```mdl
test T-4: Show enters fullscreen
  given: a Gallery is open in an article surface
  when: user clicks Show
  then: deck enters solo--fullscreen on the gallery's companion path
```
